"l5wz9inkvkf0qhl8kpl39vpg2xfm2qpy-icat.drv'.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:357
msgid ""
"A compiler error! The `icat` source was pulled from GitHub, and Nix tried to "
"build what it found, but compilation failed due to a missing dependency: the "
"`imlib2` header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:360
msgid ""
"If you [search for `imlib2` on search.nixos.org](https://search.nixos.org/"
"packages?query=imlib2), you'll find that `imlib2` is already in Nixpkgs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:362
msgid ""
"Add this package to your build environment by adding `imlib2` to the "
"arguments of the function in `icat.nix`. Then add the argument's value "
"`imlib2` to the list of `buildInputs` in `stdenv.mkDerivation`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:365
msgid ""
"# icat.nix\n"
"{\n"
"  stdenv,\n"
"  fetchFromGitHub,\n"
"  imlib2,\n"
"}:\n"
"\n"
"stdenv.mkDerivation {\n"
"  pname = \"icat\";\n"
"  version = \"v0.5\";\n"
"\n"
"  src = fetchFromGitHub {\n"
"    owner = \"atextor\";\n"
"    repo = \"icat\";\n"
"    rev = \"v0.5\";\n"
"    sha256 = \"0wyy2ksxp95vnh71ybj1bbmqd5ggp13x3mk37pzr99ljs9awy8ka\";\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  buildInputs = [ imlib2 ];\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:388
msgid ""
"Run `nix-build -A icat` again and you'll encounter another error, but "
"compilation proceeds further this time:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:390
msgid ""
"$ nix-build -A icat\n"
"this derivation will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/bw2d4rp2k1l5rg49hds199ma2mz36x47-icat.drv\n"
"...\n"
"error: builder for '/nix/store/bw2d4rp2k1l5rg49hds199ma2mz36x47-icat.drv' "
"failed with exit code 2;\n"
"       last 10 log lines:\n"
"       >                  from icat.c:31:\n"
"       > /nix/store/hkj250rjsvxcbr31fr1v81cv88cdfp4l-glibc-2.37-8-dev/"
"include/features.h:195:3: warning: #warning \"_BSD_SOURCE and _SVID_SOURCE "
"are deprecated, use _DEFAULT_SOURCE\" [8;;https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/"
"Warning-Options.html#index-Wcpp-Wcpp8;;]\n"
"       >   195 | # warning \"_BSD_SOURCE and _SVID_SOURCE are deprecated, "
"use _DEFAULT_SOURCE\"\n"
"       >       |   ^~~~~~~\n"
"       > In file included from icat.c:39:\n"
"       > /nix/store/4fvrh0sjc8sbkbqda7dfsh7q0gxmnh9p-imlib2-1.11.1-dev/"
"include/Imlib2.h:45:10: fatal error: X11/Xlib.h: No such file or directory\n"
"       >    45 | #include <X11/Xlib.h>\n"
"       >       |          ^~~~~~~~~~~~\n"
"       > compilation terminated.\n"
"       > make: *** [Makefile:16: icat.o] Error 1\n"
"       For full logs, run 'nix log /nix/store/"
"bw2d4rp2k1l5rg49hds199ma2mz36x47-icat.drv'.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:410
msgid ""
"You can see a few warnings which should be corrected in the upstream code. "
"But the important bit for this tutorial is `fatal error: X11/Xlib.h: No such "
"file or directory`: another dependency is missing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:413
msgid "Finding packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:415
msgid ""
"Determining from where to source a dependency is currently somewhat "
"involved, because package names don't always correspond to library or "
"program names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:417
msgid ""
"You will need the `Xlib.h` headers from the `X11` C package, the Nixpkgs "
"derivation for which is `libX11`, available in the `xorg` package set. There "
"are multiple ways to figure this out:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:420
msgid "`search.nixos.org`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:423
msgid "The easiest way to find what you need is on search.nixos.org/packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:426
msgid ""
"Unfortunately in this case, [searching for `x11`](https://search.nixos.org/"
"packages?query=x11) produces too many irrelevant results because X11 is "
"ubiquitous. On the left side bar there is a list package sets, and "
"[selecting `xorg`](https://search.nixos.org/packages?"
"buckets={%22package_attr_set%22%3A[%22xorg%22]%2C%22package_license_set%22%3A[]%2C%22package_maintainers_set%22%3A[]%2C%22package_platforms%22%3A[]}"
"&query=x11) shows something promising."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:429
msgid ""
"In case all else fails, it helps to become familiar with searching the "
"[Nixpkgs source code](https://github.com/nixos/nixpkgs) for keywords."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:431
msgid "Local code search"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:433
msgid ""
"To find name assignments in the source, search for `\"<keyword> =\"`. For "
"example, these are the search results for [`\"x11 = \"`](https://github.com/"
"search?q=repo%3ANixOS%2Fnixpkgs+%22x11+%3D%22&type=code) or [`\"libx11 =\"`]"
"(https://github.com/search?q=repo%3ANixOS%2Fnixpkgs+%22libx11+"
"%3D%22&type=code) on Github."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:436
msgid ""
"Or fetch a clone of the [Nixpkgs repository](https://github.com/nixos/"
"nixpkgs) and search the code locally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:438
msgid ""
"Start a shell that makes the required tools available – `git` for version "
"control, and `rg` for code search (provided by the [`ripgrep` package]"
"(https://search.nixos.org/packages?show=ripgrep)):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:439
msgid ""
"$ nix-shell -p git ripgrep\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:444
msgid ""
"The Nixpkgs repository is huge. Only clone the latest revision to avoid "
"waiting a long time for a full clone:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:447
msgid ""
"[nix-shell:~]$ git clone https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs --depth 1\n"
"...\n"
"[nix-shell:~]$ cd nixpkgs/\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:453
msgid ""
"To narrow down results, only search the `pkgs` subdirectory, which holds all "
"the package recipes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:455
msgid ""
"[nix-shell:~]$ rg \"x11 =\" pkgs\n"
"pkgs/tools/X11/primus/default.nix\n"
"21:  primus = if useNvidia then primusLib_ else primusLib_.override "
"{ nvidia_x11 = null; };\n"
"22:  primus_i686 = if useNvidia then primusLib_i686_ else primusLib_i686_."
"override { nvidia_x11 = null; };\n"
"\n"
"pkgs/applications/graphics/imv/default.nix\n"
"38:    x11 = [ libGLU xorg.libxcb xorg.libX11 ];\n"
"\n"
"pkgs/tools/X11/primus/lib.nix\n"
"14:    if nvidia_x11 == null then libGL\n"
"\n"
"pkgs/top-level/linux-kernels.nix\n"
"573:    ati_drivers_x11 = throw \"ati drivers are no longer supported by any "
"kernel >=4.1\"; # added 2021-05-18;\n"
"... <a lot more results>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:472
msgid ""
"Since `rg` is case sensitive by default, Add `-i` to make sure you don't "
"miss anything:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:475
msgid ""
"[nix-shell:~]$ rg -i \"libx11 =\" pkgs\n"
"pkgs/applications/version-management/monotone-viz/graphviz-2.0.nix\n"
"55:    ++ lib.optional (libX11 == null) \"--without-x\";\n"
"\n"
"pkgs/top-level/all-packages.nix\n"
"14191:    libX11 = xorg.libX11;\n"
"\n"
"pkgs/servers/x11/xorg/default.nix\n"
"1119:  libX11 = callPackage ({ stdenv, pkg-config, fetchurl, xorgproto, "
"libpthreadstubs, libxcb, xtrans, testers }: stdenv.mkDerivation (finalAttrs: "
"{\n"
"\n"
"pkgs/servers/x11/xorg/overrides.nix\n"
"147:  libX11 = super.libX11.overrideAttrs (attrs: {\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:490
msgid "Local derivation search"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:492
msgid ""
"To search derivations on the command line, use `nix-locate` from the [`nix-"
"index`](https://github.com/nix-community/nix-index)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:494
msgid "Adding package sets as dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:496
msgid ""
"Add `xorg` to your derivation's input attribute set and use `xorg.libX11` in "
"`buildInputs`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:498
msgid ""
"# icat.nix\n"
"{\n"
"  stdenv,\n"
"  fetchFromGitHub,\n"
"  imlib2,\n"
"  xorg,\n"
"}:\n"
"\n"
"stdenv.mkDerivation {\n"
"  pname = \"icat\";\n"
"  version = \"v0.5\";\n"
"\n"
"  src = fetchFromGitHub {\n"
"    owner = \"atextor\";\n"
"    repo = \"icat\";\n"
"    rev = \"v0.5\";\n"
"    sha256 = \"0wyy2ksxp95vnh71ybj1bbmqd5ggp13x3mk37pzr99ljs9awy8ka\";\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  buildInputs = [ imlib2 xorg.libX11 ];\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:523
msgid ""
"Because the Nix language is lazily evaluated, accessing only `xorg.libX11` "
"means that the remaining contents of the `xorg` attribute set are never "
"processed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:526
msgid "Fixing build failures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:528
msgid "Run the last command again:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:530
msgid ""
"$ nix-build -A icat\n"
"this derivation will be built:\n"
"  /nix/store/x1d79ld8jxqdla5zw2b47d2sl87mf56k-icat.drv\n"
"...\n"
"error: builder for '/nix/store/x1d79ld8jxqdla5zw2b47d2sl87mf56k-icat.drv' "
"failed with exit code 2;\n"
"       last 10 log lines:\n"
"       >   195 | # warning \"_BSD_SOURCE and _SVID_SOURCE are deprecated, "
"use _DEFAULT_SOURCE\"\n"
"       >       |   ^~~~~~~\n"
"       > icat.c: In function 'main':\n"
"       > icat.c:319:33: warning: ignoring return value of 'write' declared "
"with attribute 'warn_unused_result' [8;;https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/"
"Warning-Options.html#index-Wunused-result-Wunused-result8;;]\n"
"       >   319 |                                 write(tempfile, &buf, 1);\n"
"       >       |                                 ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n"
"       > gcc -o icat icat.o -lImlib2\n"
"       > installing\n"
"       > install flags: SHELL=/nix/store/8fv91097mbh5049i9rglc73dx6kjg3qk-"
"bash-5.2-p15/bin/bash install\n"
"       > make: *** No rule to make target 'install'.  Stop.\n"
"       For full logs, run 'nix log /nix/store/"
"x1d79ld8jxqdla5zw2b47d2sl87mf56k-icat.drv'.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:550
msgid ""
"The missing dependency error is solved, but there is now another problem: "
"`make: *** No rule to make target 'install'.  Stop.`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:552
msgid "`installPhase`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:553
msgid ""
"`stdenv` is automatically working with the `Makefile` that comes with "
"`icat`. The console output shows that `configure` and `make` are executed "
"without issue, so the `icat` binary is compiling successfully."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:556
msgid ""
"The failure occurs when the `stdenv` attempts to run `make install`. The "
"`Makefile` included in the project happens to lack an `install` target. The "
"`README` in the `icat` repository only mentions using `make` to build the "
"tool, leaving the installation step up to users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:560
msgid ""
"To add this step to your derivation, use the [`installPhase` attribute]"
"(https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#ssec-install-phase). It contains a "
"list of command strings that are executed to perform the installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:563
msgid ""
"Because `make` finishes successfully, the `icat` executable is available in "
"the build directory. You only need to copy it from there to the output "
"directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:566
msgid ""
"In Nix, the output directory is stored in the `$out` variable. That variable "
"is accessible in the derivation's [`builder` execution environment](https://"
"nix.dev/manual/nix/2.19/language/derivations#builder-execution). Create a "
"`bin` directory within the `$out` directory and copy the `icat` binary there:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:570
msgid ""
"# icat.nix\n"
"{\n"
"  stdenv,\n"
"  fetchFromGitHub,\n"
"  imlib2,\n"
"  xorg,\n"
"}:\n"
"\n"
"stdenv.mkDerivation {\n"
"  pname = \"icat\";\n"
"  version = \"v0.5\";\n"
"\n"
"  src = fetchFromGitHub {\n"
"    owner = \"atextor\";\n"
"    repo = \"icat\";\n"
"    rev = \"v0.5\";\n"
"    sha256 = \"0wyy2ksxp95vnh71ybj1bbmqd5ggp13x3mk37pzr99ljs9awy8ka\";\n"
"  };\n"
"\n"
"  buildInputs = [ imlib2 xorg.libX11 ];\n"
"\n"
"  installPhase = ''\n"
"    mkdir -p $out/bin\n"
"    cp icat $out/bin\n"
"  '';\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:599
msgid "Phases and hooks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:601
msgid ""
"Nixpkgs `stdenv.mkDerivation` derivations are separated into [phases]"
"(https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#sec-stdenv-phases). Each is "
"intended to control some aspect of the build process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:604
msgid ""
"Earlier you observed how `stdenv.mkDerivation` expected the project's "
"`Makefile` to have an `install` target, and failed when it didn't. To fix "
"this, you defined a custom `installPhase` containing instructions for "
"copying the `icat` binary to the correct output location, in effect "
"installing it. Up to that point, the `stdenv.mkDerivation` automatically "
"determined the `buildPhase` information for the `icat` package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:608
msgid ""
"During derivation realisation, there are a number of shell functions "
"(\"hooks\", in Nixpkgs) which may execute in each derivation phase. Hooks do "
"things like set variables, source files, create directories, and so on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:611
msgid ""
"These are specific to each phase, and run both before and after that phase's "
"execution. They modify the build environment for common operations during "
"the build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:614
msgid ""
"It's good practice when packaging software with Nix to include calls to "
"these hooks in the derivation phases you define, even when you don't make "
"direct use of them. This facilitates easy [overriding](https://nixos.org/"
"manual/nixpkgs/stable/#chap-overrides) of specific parts of the derivation "
"later. And it keeps the code tidy and makes it easier to read."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:618
msgid "Adjust your `installPhase` to call the appropriate hooks:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:620
msgid ""
"# icat.nix\n"
"\n"
"# ...\n"
"\n"
"  installPhase = ''\n"
"    runHook preInstall\n"
"    mkdir -p $out/bin\n"
"    cp icat $out/bin\n"
"    runHook postInstall\n"
"  '';\n"
"\n"
"# ...\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:636
msgid "A successful build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:638
msgid ""
"Running the `nix-build` command once more will finally do what you want, "
"repeatably. Call `ls` in the local directory to find a `result` symlink to a "
"location in the Nix store:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:641
msgid ""
"$ ls\n"
"default.nix hello.nix icat.nix result\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../tutorials/packaging-existing-software.md:646
msgid "`result/bin/icat` is the executable built previously. Success!"
msgstr ""

